race.comment: HAGGLER (4) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fifth (23.94) in a Grade 5 at Casino. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Has ability and is a key runner. KENNY DUTTON (3) was in the placings last time but shapes well for this on his fast win three back, getting around this track over 366m in 19.80. Smart winner three back and looks a key chance on that form. INTO OBLIVION (2) has missed the frame the last couple but was a Grade 4/5 winner three back (22.00) at Q Lakeside over 390m. Safe beginner and drawn well close to the inside. Well placed here and can atone this time. TANK ENGINE (6) can return to form after missing the top-three at this circuit last time out.
